trapVismIpAddressChanged.name: trapVismIpAddressChanged
trapVismIpAddressChanged.description: Sent when the card's IP address is changed. vismIpAddress contains the new IP address.

trapVismChanActive.name: trapVismChanActive
trapVismChanActive.description: Sent when a channel becomes active. genericLineNum is always set to 0 on the VISM card since it is not applicable to VISM. vismCnfChanNum specifies the channel number and vismChanPortNum specifies the port number where the channel is configured.

trapVismChanDeleted.name: trapVismChanDeleted
trapVismChanDeleted.description: Sent when a channel is deleted. genericLineNum is always set to 0 on the VISM card since it is not applicable to VISM. vismCnfChanNum specifies the channel number and vismChanPortNum specifies the port number where the channel is configured.

trapVismPortAdded.name: trapVismPortAdded
trapVismPortAdded.description: Indicates that a port with port number vismPortNum was added with type vismPortType.

trapVismPortActive.name: trapVismPortActive
trapVismPortActive.description: Indicates port with port number vismPortNum went active. The type of port is specified in vismPortType.

trapVismPortFailed.name: trapVismPortFailed
trapVismPortFailed.description: Indicates port with port number vismPortNum failed. The new state of the port is specified in vismPortState.

trapProtectedChanActive.name: trapProtectedChanActive
trapProtectedChanActive.description: Sent when the channel on port number vismChanPortNum with a channel number vismCnfChanNum transitions to active as specified by vismChanActivityState .

trapProtectedChanStandby.name: trapProtectedChanStandby
trapProtectedChanStandby.description: Sent when the channel on port number vismChanPortNum with a channel number vismCnfChanNum transitions to standby as specified by vismChanActivityState.

trapProtectedChanFailed.name: trapProtectedChanFailed
trapProtectedChanFailed.description: Sent when the channel on port number vismChanPortNum with a channel number vismCnfChanNum transitions to failed as specified by vismChanActivityState.

trapProtectedChanLocked.name: trapProtectedChanLocked
trapProtectedChanLocked.description: Sent when the channel on port number vismChanPortNum with a channel number vismCnfChanNum transitions to locked as specified by vismChanLockingState.

trapProtectedChanUnlocked.name: trapProtectedChanUnlocked
trapProtectedChanUnlocked.description: Sent when the channel on port number vismChanPortNum with a channel number vismCnfChanNum transitions to unlocked as specified by vismChanLockingState.

trapVismCasVariantAdded.name: trapVismCasVariantAdded
trapVismCasVariantAdded.description: Indicates that an entry has been added to vismCasVariantTable. vismCasVariantName is user defined and associated with vismCasFileName. vismCasFileName can be chosen from predefined filenames describing a CAS protocol. vismCasVariantState specifies whether the CAS variant is configured or not configured.

trapVismCasVariantDeleted.name: trapVismCasVariantDeleted
trapVismCasVariantDeleted.description: Indicates that an entry with a name vismCasVariantName has been deleted from vismCasVariantTable.

trapVismCasVariantConfigured.name: trapVismCasVariantConfigured
trapVismCasVariantConfigured.description: Indicates that vismCasVariantState transitioned to configured.

trapVismCasVariantNotConfigured.name: trapVismCasVariantNotConfigured
trapVismCasVariantNotConfigured.description: Indicates that vismCasVariantState transitioned to not configured.

trapVismScalarChange.name: trapVismScalarChange
trapVismScalarChange.description: Sent when a scalar object/objects changes. The bit map indicates the group to which the changed object/objects belong. For a single set operation, a single trap will be sent per group, regardless of how many objects got changed in in that group.

trapVismTableChange.name: trapVismTableChange
trapVismTableChange.description: Sent when a table config has changed. The bit map tells which table got changed. and vismTrapIntIndex1 shows the index of the table entry which got changed. If there are 2 index values, the 2nd index will be contained in vismTrapIntIndex2. If the table has a string index, the index value will be contained in vismTrapStrIndex1.

trapVismCodecTemplateChanged.name: trapVismCodecTemplateChanged
trapVismCodecTemplateChanged.description: Indicates that the VISM Codec template has been changed. vismAppliedTemplate is the new template number.

trapVismModeChanged.name: trapVismModeChanged
trapVismModeChanged.description: Indicates that the mode has been changed on the card. vismMode specifies the new mode of the card.

trapVismAal2CidAdded.name: trapVismAal2CidAdded
trapVismAal2CidAdded.description: Indicates that a CID vismAal2CidNum has been added to an LCN vismAal2CidLcn thereby creating an entry in the vismAal2CidCnfTable.

trapVismAal2CidDeleted.name: trapVismAal2CidDeleted
trapVismAal2CidDeleted.description: Indicates that a CID vismAal2CidNum has been deleted from an LCN vismAal2CidLcn thereby deleting the corresponding entry from the table vismAal2CidCnfTable.

trapVismHdlcChanAdded.name: trapVismHdlcChanAdded
trapVismHdlcChanAdded.description: Indicates that an entry with HDLC channel number vismHdlcChanNum has been added to the table vismHdlcChanTable.

trapVismHdlcChanDeleted.name: trapVismHdlcChanDeleted
trapVismHdlcChanDeleted.description: Indicates that an entry with HDLC channel number vismHdlcChanNum has been deleted from the table vismHdlcChanTable.

trapVismPortDeleted.name: trapVismPortDeleted
trapVismPortDeleted.description: Indicates port with port number vismPortNum has been deleted.

trapVismChanAdded.name: trapVismChanAdded
trapVismChanAdded.description: Sent when a VISM Channel is added, genericLineNum is always set to 0 since it is not applicable to VISM.

trapVismChanFailed.name: trapVismChanFailed
trapVismChanFailed.description: Sent when a VISM Channel fails, genericLineNum is always set to 0 since it is not applicable to VISM.

trapVismConDown.name: trapVismConDown
trapVismConDown.description: Sent when a PVC is brought down.

trapVismConUp.name: trapVismConUp
trapVismConUp.description: Sent when a PVC is brought up from down. The previous vismChanRowStatus of this channel must be outOfService.

trapVismChanReroute.name: trapVismChanReroute
trapVismChanReroute.description: Sent when a VISM Channel is rerouted.

trapVismAal2Muxing.name: trapVismAal2Muxing
trapVismAal2Muxing.description: Sent when aal2 muxing type is changed. vismAal2SubcellMuxing will represent whether subcell muxing is enabled or disabled.

trapVismCidState.name: trapVismCidState
trapVismCidState.description: Sent when there is a state change on vismAal2CidNum in the LCN specified by vismAal2CidLcn to a new state specified in vismAal2CidState with the reason vismAal2CidFailReason. For example, if a PVC alarm is generated on the remote end for vismAal2CidLcn, all vismAal2CidNum within this LCN with transition to a failed state as specified in vismAal2CidState.

trapNetworkCacConfigState.name: trapNetworkCacConfigState
trapNetworkCacConfigState.description: This trap is sent when networkCacConfigState changes.

trapVismFeatureChanged.name: trapVismFeatureChanged
trapVismFeatureChanged.description: By changing the mode of the card you can change the usable feature set on the card. This trap is sent when the vismFeatureBitMap has been changed on the card.

trapAvailFreeDs0Low.name: trapAvailFreeDs0Low
trapAvailFreeDs0Low.description: Indicates available free DS0 on the card are low.

mgAdministrativeStateLocked.name: mgAdministrativeStateLocked
mgAdministrativeStateLocked.description: Triggered when mgAdministrativeState transitions to locked. The transition may be from unlocked to locked or from 'gracefulOutOfService' to locked.

mgAdministrativeStateUnlocked.name: mgAdministrativeStateUnlocked
mgAdministrativeStateUnlocked.description: Triggered when mgAdministrativeState transitions from locked to unlocked.

mgAdministrativeStateShuttingDown.name: mgAdministrativeStateShuttingDown
mgAdministrativeStateShuttingDown.description: Triggered when mgAdministrativeState transitions from unlocked to 'gracefulOutOfService'.

mgcAssociated.name: mgcAssociated
mgcAssociated.description: Triggered when mgAssociationState transitions to associated. The transition may be from unassociated to associated or from associatedCommLoss to associated. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of mgcNumber.

mgcUnassociated.name: mgcUnassociated
mgcUnassociated.description: Triggered when mgAssociationState transitions to Unassociated. The transition may be from associated to Unassociated or from associatedCommLoss to Unassociated. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of mgcNumber.

mgcAssociatedCommLoss.name: mgcAssociatedCommLoss
mgcAssociatedCommLoss.description: Triggered when mgAssociationState transitions from associated to associatedCommLoss. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of mgcNumber.

mgcCommStateActive.name: mgcCommStateActive
mgcCommStateActive.description: Triggered when mgcResolutionCommState transitions from inactive to active. Indicates that an IP address of an MGC has become active. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of mgcResolutionIndex.

mgcCommStateInactive.name: mgcCommStateInactive
mgcCommStateInactive.description: Triggered when mgcResolutionCommState transitions from active to inactive. Indicates that an IP address of an MGC has become inactive. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of mgcResolutionIndex.

mgEndpointCreated.name: mgEndpointCreated
mgEndpointCreated.description: Triggered by creation of an endpoint. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of mgEndpointNumber.

mgEndpointDeleted.name: mgEndpointDeleted
mgEndpointDeleted.description: Triggered by deletion of an endpoint. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of mgEndpointNumber.

mgEndpointActive.name: mgEndpointActive
mgEndpointActive.description: Triggered when mgEndpointState transitions from failed/degraded to active. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of mgEndpointNumber.

mgEndpointFailed.name: mgEndpointFailed
mgEndpointFailed.description: Triggered when mgEndpointState transitions from active to failed/degraded. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of mgEndpointNumber.

mgcAdded.name: mgcAdded
mgcAdded.description: Indicates that an entry is added to mgcTable. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of mgcNumber.

mgcDeleted.name: mgcDeleted
mgcDeleted.description: Indicates that an entry is deleted from mgcTable. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of mgcNumber.

mgcProtocolAdded.name: mgcProtocolAdded
mgcProtocolAdded.description: Indicates that an entry is added to mgcProtocolTable. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of mgcNumber. The value of vismTrapIntIndex2 gives the value of mgProtocolNumber.

mgcProtocolDeleted.name: mgcProtocolDeleted
mgcProtocolDeleted.description: Indicates that an entry is deleted from mgcProtocolTable. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of mgcNumber. The value of vismTrapIntIndex2 gives the value of mgProtocolNumber.

mgcResolutionAdded.name: mgcResolutionAdded
mgcResolutionAdded.description: Indicates that an entry is added to mgcResolutionTable. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of mgcResolutionIndex.

mgcResolutionDeleted.name: mgcResolutionDeleted
mgcResolutionDeleted.description: Indicates that an entry is deleted from mgcResolutionTable. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of mgcResolutionIndex.

peerHeartbeatLost.name: peerHeartbeatLost
peerHeartbeatLost.description: This notification indicates that the system failed to receive a heartbeat from a specific peer. The notification is sent when srcpPeerTimeSinceHeartbeat crosses the srcpPeerHeartbeatInterval threshold. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of srcpPeerId.

peerHeartbeatDetected.name: peerHeartbeatDetected
peerHeartbeatDetected.description: This notification indicates that the system detected a heartbeat from a specific peer after it had been lost. The notification is sent when srcpPeerTimeSinceHeartbeat which had exceeded the threshold, resets to 0 due to receipt of a heartbeat. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of srcpPeerId.

trapLapdAdded.name: trapLapdAdded
trapLapdAdded.description: Indicates that an entry has been added to vismLapdTable with an index vismLapdIndex.

trapLapdDeleted.name: trapLapdDeleted
trapLapdDeleted.description: Indicates that the entry with index vismLapdIndex has been deleted from vismLapdTable.

trapSessionSetAdded.name: trapSessionSetAdded
trapSessionSetAdded.description: Indicates that an entry has been added to vismSessionSetTable.

trapSessionSetDeleted.name: trapSessionSetDeleted
trapSessionSetDeleted.description: Indicates that an entry has been deleted from vismSessionSetTable.

trapSessionGrpAdded.name: trapSessionGrpAdded
trapSessionGrpAdded.description: Indicates that an entry has been added to vismSessionGrpTable.

trapSessionGrpDeleted.name: trapSessionGrpDeleted
trapSessionGrpDeleted.description: Indicates that an entry has been deleted from vismSessionGrpTable.

trapRudpSessionAdded.name: trapRudpSessionAdded
trapRudpSessionAdded.description: Indicates that an entry has been added to vismRudpSessionCnfTable.

trapRudpSessionDeleted.name: trapRudpSessionDeleted
trapRudpSessionDeleted.description: Indicates that an entry has been deleted from vismRudpSessionCnfTable.

trapRudpSessionOos.name: trapRudpSessionOos
trapRudpSessionOos.description: When a session loses communication with the MGC the state changes to 'Out Of Service' and sends out this trap. The severity of this trap should be minor severity.

trapRudpSessionIs.name: trapRudpSessionIs
trapRudpSessionIs.description: When a session state changes to 'In Service' this trap is sent out. The severity should be informational.

trapRudpSessionPrimaryIs.name: trapRudpSessionPrimaryIs
trapRudpSessionPrimaryIs.description: This trap is sent out when the session state is changed to 'Primary In Service'. The severity should be informational.

trapRudpSessionActive.name: trapRudpSessionActive
trapRudpSessionActive.description: When a 'Primary In Service' session in a group receives active message from the MGC this trap will be sent out. The severity should be informational.

trapSessionGrpOos.name: trapSessionGrpOos
trapSessionGrpOos.description: When all the sessions in the group have changed to 'Out Of Service' state, the state of this group is changed to 'Out Of Service' and this trap will be sent out. The severity should be 'minor', no alarm.

trapSessionGrpIs.name: trapSessionGrpIs
trapSessionGrpIs.description: When the state of this group is changed to 'In Service' this trap will be sent out. The severity should be informational.

trapSessionSetOos.name: trapSessionSetOos
trapSessionSetOos.description: When the session set state is changed to 'Out Of Service' this trap will be sent out. The severity should be 'minor', no alarm.

trapSessionSetActiveIs.name: trapSessionSetActiveIs
trapSessionSetActiveIs.description: When the session set state is changed to 'Active In Service' state this trap will be sent out. The severity should be informational.

trapSessionSetStandbyIs.name: trapSessionSetStandbyIs
trapSessionSetStandbyIs.description: When the session set state is changed to 'Standby In Service' state this trap will be sent out. The severity should be informational.

trapSessionSetFullIs.name: trapSessionSetFullIs
trapSessionSetFullIs.description: When the session set state is changed from other state to 'Full In Service' state this trap will be sent out. The severity should be informational.

trapLapdDlcAdded.name: trapLapdDlcAdded
trapLapdDlcAdded.description: Indicates that an entry has been added to vismLapdDlcTable.

trapLapdDlcDeleted.name: trapLapdDlcDeleted
trapLapdDlcDeleted.description: Indicates that an entry has been deleted from vismLapdDlcTable.

trapLapdDlcUp.name: trapLapdDlcUp
trapLapdDlcUp.description: Indicates that the linking state between TDM and DLC on a specific D-channel changes to up.

trapLapdDlcDown.name: trapLapdDlcDown
trapLapdDlcDown.description: Indicates that the linking state between TDM and DLC on a specific D-channel changes to down.

persistentXgcpEventCreated.name: persistentXgcpEventCreated
persistentXgcpEventCreated.description: Indicates that an entry is added to persistantXgcpEvents table. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of persistentXgcpEventNum. persistentXgcpEventName gives the name associated with that event num.

persistentXgcpEventDeleted.name: persistentXgcpEventDeleted
persistentXgcpEventDeleted.description: Indicates that an entry is deleted from persistantXgcpEvents table. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of persistantXgcpEventNum. The varbind persistantXgcpEventName gives the name associated with that event num.

mgDomainNameAdded.name: mgDomainNameAdded
mgDomainNameAdded.description: Indicates that an entry is added to mgDomainNameTable.

mgDomainNameDeleted.name: mgDomainNameDeleted
mgDomainNameDeleted.description: Indicates that an entry is deleted from mgDomainNameTable. vismTrapIntIndex1 specifies the mgDomainNameIndex.

vismTonePlanAdded.name: vismTonePlanAdded
vismTonePlanAdded.description: Indicates that an entry is added to vismTonePlanTable. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of tonePlanIndex.

vismTonePlanDeleted.name: vismTonePlanDeleted
vismTonePlanDeleted.description: Indicates that an entry is deleted from vismTonePlanTable. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of tonePlanIndex.

vismRtpConnAdded.name: vismRtpConnAdded
vismRtpConnAdded.description: Indicates that an entry has been added to vismRtpConnGrpTable with vismRtpLcn. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the vismRtpConnNum.

vismRtpConnDeleted.name: vismRtpConnDeleted
vismRtpConnDeleted.description: Indicates that an entry with Lcn vismRtpLcn has been deleted from vismRtpConnGrpTable. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the vismRtpConnNum.

vismRtpConnStateChg.name: vismRtpConnStateChg
vismRtpConnStateChg.description: Indicates that the alarm state of the entry in vismRtpConnGrpTable with LCN vismRtpLcn changed. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the vismRtpConnNum.

vismLapdTrStateIs.name: vismLapdTrStateIs
vismLapdTrStateIs.description: Indicates that the LAPD Trunk state has changed to 'In Service'. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of vismLapdTrunkNum.

vismLapdTrStateOos.name: vismLapdTrStateOos
vismLapdTrStateOos.description: Indicates that the LAPD Trunk state has changed to 'Out Of Service'. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of vismLapdTrunkNum.

vismLapdTrunkAdded.name: vismLapdTrunkAdded
vismLapdTrunkAdded.description: Indicates that a new entry has been added to the vismLapdTrunkGrpTable. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of vismLapdTrunkNum.

vismLapdTrunkDeleted.name: vismLapdTrunkDeleted
vismLapdTrunkDeleted.description: Indicates that an existing entry has been deleted from the vismLapdTrunkGrpTable. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of vismLapdTrunkNum.

mgcRedundancyGrpAdded.name: mgcRedundancyGrpAdded
mgcRedundancyGrpAdded.description: Indicates that an entry has been added in the mgcRedundancyGrptable. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of mgcRedundancyGrpNum and vismTrapIntIndex2 gives the value of mgcNumber.

mgcRedundancyGrpDeleted.name: mgcRedundancyGrpDeleted
mgcRedundancyGrpDeleted.description: Indicates that an entry has been deleted from the mgcRedudancyGrpTable. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of mgcRedundancyGrpNum and vismTrapIntIndex2 gives the value of mgcNumber.

mgcRedundancyGrpCommOk.name: mgcRedundancyGrpCommOk
mgcRedundancyGrpCommOk.description: Triggered when the communication state of the MGC redundancy group transitions to 'commOk' state. The transition will be from 'commLoss' to 'commOk' when communication between the gateway and the call agent is established. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of mgcRedundancyGrpNum.

mgcRedundancyGrpCommLoss.name: mgcRedundancyGrpCommLoss
mgcRedundancyGrpCommLoss.description: Triggered when the communication state of the MGC redundancy group transitions to 'commLoss'. The transition will be from 'commOk' to 'commLoss' when the callagent does not respond to gateway initiated messages. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of mgcRedundancyGrpNum.

mgcActiveInGrp.name: mgcActiveInGrp
mgcActiveInGrp.description: Triggered when the MGC in an MGC Redundancy Group transitions from inactive to active state. Indicates the active MGC in an MGC Redundancy group. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of mgcRedundancyGrpNum. The value of vismTrapIntIndex2 gives the value of mgcNumber.

mgcInactiveInGrp.name: mgcInactiveInGrp
mgcInactiveInGrp.description: Triggered when the MGC in an MGC Redundancy Group transitions from active to inactive state. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of mgcRedundancyGrpNum. The value of vismTrapIntIndex2 gives the value of mgcNumber.

mgcRedundancyGrpProtocolAdded.name: mgcRedundancyGrpProtocolAdded
mgcRedundancyGrpProtocolAdded.description: Indicates that an entry is added to the mgcRedundancyGrpProtocolTable. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of mgcRedundancyGrpNum. The value of vismTrapIntIndex2 gives the value of mgProtocolNumber.

mgcRedundancyGrpProtocolDeleted.name: mgcRedundancyGrpProtocolDeleted
mgcRedundancyGrpProtocolDeleted.description: Indicates that an entry is deleted from the mgcRedundancyGrpProtocolTable. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of mgcRedundancyGrpNum. The value of vismTrapIntIndex2 gives the value of mgProtocolNumber.

peerGrpHeartbeatLost.name: peerGrpHeartbeatLost
peerGrpHeartbeatLost.description: This notification indicates that the system failed to receive a heartbeat from a specific peer group. The notification is sent when srcpPeerGrpTimeSinceHeartbeat crosses the srcpPeerGrpHeartbeatInterval threshold. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of mgcRedundancyGrpNum.

peerGrpHeartbeatDetected.name: peerGrpHeartbeatDetected
peerGrpHeartbeatDetected.description: This notification indicates that the system detected a heartbeat from a specific peer group after it had been lost. The notification is sent when srcpPeerGrpTimeSinceHeartbeat which had exceeded the threshold, resets to 0 due to receipt of a heartbeat. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of mgcRedundancyGrpNum.

mgcRedundancyGrpParamEntryAdded.name: mgcRedundancyGrpParamEntryAdded
mgcRedundancyGrpParamEntryAdded.description: Indicates that an entry has been added in the mgcRedundancyGrpParamTable. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of mgcRedundancyGrpNum. The entries in the mgcRedundancyGrpParamTable are implicitly added when the first entry for that mgcRedundancyGrpNum is added into the mgcRedundancyGrpTable by the user.

mgcRedundancyGrpParamEntryDeleted.name: mgcRedundancyGrpParamEntryDeleted
mgcRedundancyGrpParamEntryDeleted.description: Indicates that an entry has been deleted from the mgcRedundancyGrpParamTable. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of mgcRedundancyGrpNum. The entries in the mgcRedundancyGrpParamTable are implicitly deleted when the last entry for that mgcRedundancyGrpNum is removed from the mgcRedundancyGrpTable by the user.

srcpPeerGrpParamEntryAdded.name: srcpPeerGrpParamEntryAdded
srcpPeerGrpParamEntryAdded.description: Indicates that an entry has been added to the srcpPeerGrpParamTable. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of mgcRedundancyGrpNum. The entries in the srcpPeerGrpParamTable are implicitly created when SRCP protocol is added for the MGC Redundancy Group.

srcpPeerGrpParamEntryDeleted.name: srcpPeerGrpParamEntryDeleted
srcpPeerGrpParamEntryDeleted.description: Indicates that an entry has been deleted from the srcpPeerGrpParamTable. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of mgcRedundancyGrpNum. The entries in the srcpPeerGrpParamTable are implicitly deleted when the SRCP protocol configured for the Mgc Redundancy Group is deleted.

cwAnnFileAddStarted.name: cwAnnFileAddStarted
cwAnnFileAddStarted.description: Indicates that an attempt was made to add an entry to the cwAnnounceTable. This trap will not be generated at card reset time when all of previously configured permanent files are downloaded to bring the card up to date. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of cwAnnounceIndex.

cwAnnFileLoadComplete.name: cwAnnFileLoadComplete
cwAnnFileLoadComplete.description: Indicates that an attempt to add an entry to the cwAnnounceTable has been successfully completed. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of cwAnnounceIndex.

cwAnnFileLoadFailed.name: cwAnnFileLoadFailed
cwAnnFileLoadFailed.description: Indicates that an attempt to add an entry to the cwAnnounceTable has failed. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of cwAnnounceIndex.

cwAnnFileDeleted.name: cwAnnFileDeleted
cwAnnFileDeleted.description: Indicates that an entry is deleted from cwAnnounceTable. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of cwAnnounceIndex.

newFlow.name: newFlow
newFlow.description: The newFlow trap indicates that the originating system has installed a new flow in its classifier, or (when reservation authorization is in view) is prepared to install such a flow in the classifier and is requesting authorization. The objects included with the notification may be used to read further information using the Integrated Services and RSVP MIBs. Authorization or non- authorization may be enacted by a write to the variable intSrvFlowStatus.

lostFlow.name: lostFlow
lostFlow.description: The lostFlow trap indicates that the originating system has removed a flow from its classifier.

dspRASEndpointFailed.name: dspRASEndpointFailed
dspRASEndpointFailed.description: Triggered by DSP channel failure associated with an endpoint. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of mgEndpointNumber.

dspRASEndpointActive.name: dspRASEndpointActive
dspRASEndpointActive.description: Triggered by DSP channel associated with an endpoint after a channel failure corrected by the DSP. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of mgEndpointNumber.

vismConfigToneDetectAdded.name: vismConfigToneDetectAdded
vismConfigToneDetectAdded.description: Indicates that an entry is added to vismConfigToneDetectTable. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of vismConfigToneDetectNum.

vismConfigToneDetectDeleted.name: vismConfigToneDetectDeleted
vismConfigToneDetectDeleted.description: Indicates that an entry is deleted from vismConfigToneDetectTable. The value of vismTrapIntIndex1 gives the value of vismConfigToneDetectNum.

trapCidAdministrativeStateChange.name: trapCidAdministrativeStateChange
trapCidAdministrativeStateChange.description: Indicates that the CID or bearer connection has either changed state from CidInService to CidCommandedOutOfService or vice versa.

vismCasTransTblAdded.name: vismCasTransTblAdded
vismCasTransTblAdded.description: Indicates that an entry is added to the cvcmABCDBitTemplateConfigTable. vismTrapIntIndex1 will contain the cvcmCasTemplateIndex and vismTrapIntIndex2 will contain the cvcmABCDPatternIndex. cvcmCasTemplateName will indicate the name of the CAS template added.

vismCasTranTblDeleted.name: vismCasTranTblDeleted
vismCasTranTblDeleted.description: Indicates that an entry is deleted from the cvcmABCDBitTemplateConfigTable. vismTrapIntIndex1 will contain the cvcmCasTemplateIndex and vismTrapIntIndex2 will contain the cvcmABCDPatternIndex. cvcmCasTemplateName will indicate the name of the CAS template deleted.
